    <p class="lead">The best coffee grind size for espresso is fine enough to slow the shot down and build sweetness, but not so fine that your machine starts choking like it is trying to sip a milkshake through a cocktail straw. In real life, that means starting near table-salt fine, then nudging your burr grinder based on how the shot tastes and flows.</p>
