    <p><strong>Start fine, then adjust by taste.</strong> If your shot runs fast and tastes sour or thin, go a little finer. If it runs slow and tastes bitter, dry, or harsh, go a little coarser. Keep your dose and yield the same while you adjust, or you will end up chasing your own tail.</p>
    <p>A simple starting point is 18 grams of coffee in, 36 grams of espresso out, in around 25 to 32 seconds. That is not magic. It is just a stable place to begin so your grinder setting makes sense from shot to shot.</p>
